  "artwork_generated_url": "",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.18,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.18,
      "end": 21.84,
      "text": "자막 없이 영화를 볼 수 있는 그날까지"
    },
    {
      "start": 21.84,
      "end": 23.52,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬 타임"
    },
    {
      "start": 23.52,
      "end": 29.5,
      "text": "4월에 함께하고 있는 영화는 하루하루를 플렉스하던 상속 강아지 트러블이"
    },
    {
      "start": 29.5,
      "end": 35.42,
      "text": "난생 처음 바깥세상에 나가게 되면서 새로운 주인을 찾는 이야기를 담고 있는 애니메이션"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.42,
      "end": 36.24,
      "text": "트러블"
    },
    {
      "start": 36.24,
      "end": 38.08,
      "text": "굿모닝입니다"
    },
    {
      "start": 38.08,
      "end": 39.04,
      "text": "굿모닝"
    },
    {
      "start": 39.04,
      "end": 46.32,
      "text": "4385님께서도 크리스 굿모닝입니다. 환영해요. 웃음 웃음 이렇게 보내주셨어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 46.48,
      "end": 48.76,
      "text": "Glad to be here. Thanks for the greeting."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.02,
      "end": 52.76,
      "text": "그렇죠. 이렇게 스윗한 메시지가 너무너무 기분이 좋아집니다. 그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 53.12,
      "end": 59.04,
      "text": "우리 주인공 트러블의 경우에도 우여곡절 끝에 집으로 돌아왔잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 59.04,
      "end": 62.16,
      "text": "그런데 실제로 이런 동물들이 종종 있죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 62.16,
      "end": 74.0,
      "text": "그런 케이스가 있다고 들었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.0,
      "end": 78.4,
      "text": "Yeah. The most common case that I've heard of is, of course, dogs."
    },
    {
      "start": 78.8,
      "end": 83.5,
      "text": "Oh. Dogs have a really amazing ability to find their way home."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.58,
      "end": 84.84,
      "text": "그러니까요. 너무 신기해요."
    },
    {
      "start": 84.84,
      "end": 87.56,
      "text": "There was one famous dog in the U.S."
    },
    {
      "start": 87.56,
      "end": 90.06,
      "text": "named Bobby the Wonder Dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 90.36,
      "end": 91.56,
      "text": "이게 이름이에요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 91.88,
      "end": 92.86,
      "text": "Well, Bobby."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.02,
      "end": 93.76,
      "text": "아, Bobby."
    },
    {
      "start": 93.94,
      "end": 96.78,
      "text": "And I think his nickname, Bobby the Wonder Dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 97.4,
      "end": 99.4,
      "text": "너무 amazing한 일을 했으니까."
    },
    {
      "start": 99.4,
      "end": 99.92,
      "text": "아, 예."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.18,
      "end": 103.54,
      "text": "Anyway, he lived way back in the 1920s."
    },
    {
      "start": 103.62,
      "end": 103.82,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.06,
      "end": 105.18,
      "text": "Born in 1921."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.36,
      "end": 105.7,
      "text": "Mm-hmm."
    },
    {
      "start": 105.86,
      "end": 109.52,
      "text": "And his family, his owners, they went on vacation."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.78,
      "end": 109.94,
      "text": "Mm-hmm."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.94,
      "end": 113.06,
      "text": "They brought him all the way to Oregon."
    },
    {
      "start": 113.26,
      "end": 113.64,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.16,
      "end": 115.7,
      "text": "And, uh, was it Oregon?"
    },
    {
      "start": 115.92,
      "end": 116.06,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 116.06,
      "end": 117.08,
      "text": "Oh, no. They went to Indiana."
    },
    {
      "start": 117.32,
      "end": 117.74,
      "text": "Indiana?"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.18,
      "end": 119.0,
      "text": "Went to Indiana."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.12,
      "end": 119.32,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 119.64,
      "end": 120.36,
      "text": "From Oregon."
    },
    {
      "start": 120.52,
      "end": 120.96,
      "text": "Uh-huh."
    },
    {
      "start": 121.22,
      "end": 122.68,
      "text": "And he got lost."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.1,
      "end": 123.6,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.68,
      "end": 127.42,
      "text": "And the owners were like, uh-oh, where is he? We can't find him."
    },
    {
      "start": 127.42,
      "end": 130.48,
      "text": "But they went back home without their doggie."
    },
    {
      "start": 130.58,
      "end": 130.9,
      "text": "Oh, mona."
    },
    {
      "start": 130.98,
      "end": 131.6,
      "text": "Without Bobby."
    },
    {
      "start": 131.78,
      "end": 132.14,
      "text": "Oh, mona."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.26,
      "end": 134.86,
      "text": "And Bobby went all the way back."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.94,
      "end": 135.44,
      "text": "Oh, my gosh."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.52,
      "end": 137.04,
      "text": "All the way back to Oregon."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.2,
      "end": 137.64,
      "text": "Amazing."
    },
    {
      "start": 137.78,
      "end": 139.0,
      "text": "Returned home by himself."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.26,
      "end": 139.66,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 139.88,
      "end": 142.02,
      "text": "And apparently he walked most of the way."
    },
    {
      "start": 142.26,
      "end": 145.3,
      "text": "It's a huge journey, over 2,500 miles."
    },
    {
      "start": 145.44,
      "end": 145.64,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 146.18,
      "end": 149.86,
      "text": "And, you know, dogs have a great sense of smell."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.12,
      "end": 150.38,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.42,
      "end": 150.56,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 150.7,
      "end": 151.3,
      "text": "This hugak."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.38,
      "end": 151.64,
      "text": "Mm-hmm."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.68,
      "end": 152.74,
      "text": "Great sense of smell."
    },
    {
      "start": 152.82,
      "end": 153.02,
      "text": "Mm-hmm."
    },
    {
      "start": 153.02,
      "end": 155.5,
      "text": "So he went to every rest stop."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.62,
      "end": 155.82,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 155.82,
      "end": 156.86,
      "text": "The family was driving."
    },
    {
      "start": 156.86,
      "end": 157.2,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 157.2,
      "end": 159.98,
      "text": "They stopped at rest stops to get gas and sleep."
    },
    {
      "start": 160.18,
      "end": 161.32,
      "text": "So, yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 161.48,
      "end": 162.6,
      "text": "대단한 능력이네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 163.02,
      "end": 167.32,
      "text": "아니, it's really a long way from Oregon to Indiana."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.54,
      "end": 167.78,
      "text": "그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 167.86,
      "end": 168.4,
      "text": "Super long."
    },
    {
      "start": 168.76,
      "end": 173.94,
      "text": "거의 뭐 동쪽, 서쪽 미국 땅에서 어마어마한 거리잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.06,
      "end": 175.92,
      "text": "Across the, almost the whole U.S."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.94,
      "end": 176.78,
      "text": "거의, 그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.0,
      "end": 178.14,
      "text": "Almost 3,000 miles."
    },
    {
      "start": 178.3,
      "end": 183.06,
      "text": "와, 3,000 miles가 거의 될 정도로 그 거리가 멀었는데,"
    },
    {
      "start": 183.06,
      "end": 188.72,
      "text": "와, 진짜 sense of smell 덕분에 찾게 된 게 아닐까라고 추측을 하게 합니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 188.72,
      "end": 192.02,
      "text": "And the dog became a national hero, like a celebrity."
    },
    {
      "start": 192.4,
      "end": 194.98,
      "text": "There was a movie made out of this."
    },
    {
      "start": 195.12,
      "end": 195.7,
      "text": "Oh, really?"
    },
    {
      "start": 195.7,
      "end": 203.12,
      "text": "And he lived, he didn't live too long, just six years, but he had a great, fantastic life."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.18,
      "end": 203.48,
      "text": "와."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.68,
      "end": 206.28,
      "text": "And many people were in awe of his ability."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.4,
      "end": 206.7,
      "text": "와."
    },
    {
      "start": 206.7,
      "end": 207.38,
      "text": "And dog."
    },
    {
      "start": 207.5,
      "end": 210.0,
      "text": "Dogs always have the way, the ability to find their way home."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.04,
      "end": 212.98,
      "text": "정말 어메이징한 동물인 것 같아요, 그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 213.42,
      "end": 215.6,
      "text": "네, 오늘 장면 내용 먼저 듣고 올게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 215.6,
      "end": 218.49,
      "text": "Looks like Trouble has made his choice."
    },
    {
      "start": 219.13,
      "end": 223.91,
      "text": "Mrs. Vanderhoosie always wanted Trouble to go to someone who loved him"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.91,
      "end": 225.41,
      "text": "and would give him a happy home."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.21,
      "end": 228.47,
      "text": "All that remains is to make it official."
    },
    {
      "start": 229.28,
      "end": 231.96,
      "text": "Wait, this means Trouble is mine?"
    },
    {
      "start": 232.38,
      "end": 234.64,
      "text": "Not just Trouble, but all of it."
    },
    {
      "start": 234.84,
      "end": 237.9,
      "text": "The mansion, the assets, and her fortune."
    },
    {
      "start": 238.42,
      "end": 241.52,
      "text": "But, I wouldn't know what to do with all that."
    },
    {
      "start": 241.52,
      "end": 243.0,
      "text": "All I really want is him."
    },
    {
      "start": 244.17,
      "end": 244.37,
      "text": "와."
    },
    {
      "start": 244.37,
      "end": 249.33,
      "text": "와, 서로들, 트러블의 주인이 자기다라고 주장을 하는 그런 상황에서"
    },
    {
      "start": 249.33,
      "end": 251.45,
      "text": "그 집행관 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 251.73,
      "end": 255.87,
      "text": "The executor decided to let him pick his owner."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.01,
      "end": 256.37,
      "text": "Oh."
    },
    {
      "start": 256.49,
      "end": 257.19,
      "text": "Yeah, of his own."
    },
    {
      "start": 257.31,
      "end": 259.49,
      "text": "He gave the dog the choice."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.63,
      "end": 259.85,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.01,
      "end": 260.65,
      "text": "You choose."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.77,
      "end": 260.99,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 260.99,
      "end": 261.97,
      "text": "The choice is yours."
    },
    {
      "start": 262.09,
      "end": 262.83,
      "text": "엄청난 겁니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 263.07,
      "end": 264.81,
      "text": "강아지한테 주인을 선택하라라고."
    },
    {
      "start": 265.11,
      "end": 267.49,
      "text": "So, how does he do that?"
    },
    {
      "start": 267.49,
      "end": 271.49,
      "text": "So, Trouble just jumped into Joy's arms."
    },
    {
      "start": 271.63,
      "end": 273.17,
      "text": "아, true love."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.17,
      "end": 279.13,
      "text": "정말 그 강아지가 조의의 품에 와락 달려서 안기던 그 장면이 너무 감동이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 279.13,
      "end": 280.57,
      "text": "I choose you."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.79,
      "end": 282.55,
      "text": "Zoe, pizza delivery girl."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.69,
      "end": 282.89,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 283.93,
      "end": 284.33,
      "text": "Singer."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.67,
      "end": 285.95,
      "text": "You're going to be a singer."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.11,
      "end": 286.35,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 286.35,
      "end": 290.41,
      "text": "아무튼 어떤 표현들이 있었는지 미리 알아볼까요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 291.13,
      "end": 292.47,
      "text": "Make it official."
    },
    {
      "start": 292.71,
      "end": 293.73,
      "text": "많이 들어봤죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 293.85,
      "end": 294.21,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.45,
      "end": 295.45,
      "text": "Let's make it official."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.65,
      "end": 298.97,
      "text": "공식화하다 라는 동사적인 표현입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.43,
      "end": 303.49,
      "text": "Confirmation in public이라고 생각하여도 괜찮겠죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 303.49,
      "end": 305.39,
      "text": "Usually, you do it in public."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.59,
      "end": 308.11,
      "text": "Or when you make it official, it is public."
    },
    {
      "start": 308.27,
      "end": 308.63,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 308.83,
      "end": 309.83,
      "text": "A relationship too."
    },
    {
      "start": 309.83,
      "end": 311.59,
      "text": "You can date someone."
    },
    {
      "start": 312.11,
      "end": 313.05,
      "text": "Like 비밀연애 하다가."
    },
    {
      "start": 313.27,
      "end": 314.85,
      "text": "공식 커플이 되는 거죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.03,
      "end": 315.37,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 315.55,
      "end": 315.95,
      "text": "그래요."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.07,
      "end": 317.99,
      "text": "Hey, baby, let's make it official."
    },
    {
      "start": 318.39,
      "end": 319.25,
      "text": "I like you."
    },
    {
      "start": 319.29,
      "end": 320.83,
      "text": "너무 와닿는 예문이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 320.93,
      "end": 321.27,
      "text": "그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 321.45,
      "end": 321.59,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 321.87,
      "end": 322.37,
      "text": "다행이에요."
    },
    {
      "start": 322.45,
      "end": 324.23,
      "text": "이런 분들 분명히 계실 거란 말이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.53,
      "end": 324.67,
      "text": "어?"
    },
    {
      "start": 324.73,
      "end": 325.27,
      "text": "우리 얘긴데?"
    },
    {
      "start": 325.47,
      "end": 325.77,
      "text": "이런 거."
    },
    {
      "start": 325.95,
      "end": 326.27,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 326.53,
      "end": 328.97,
      "text": "저도 뭐 한때는 비밀연애 했었죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 328.97,
      "end": 329.21,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.57,
      "end": 331.23,
      "text": "And then we finally made it official."
    },
    {
      "start": 331.39,
      "end": 332.99,
      "text": "아, made it official."
    },
    {
      "start": 333.15,
      "end": 335.47,
      "text": "이렇게 과거 시제로도 활용이 가능하겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 336.45,
      "end": 337.65,
      "text": "The assets."
    },
    {
      "start": 337.83,
      "end": 338.97,
      "text": "The assets."
    },
    {
      "start": 339.25,
      "end": 339.37,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 339.37,
      "end": 339.97,
      "text": "아, 두개 되죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 340.11,
      "end": 340.35,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 340.85,
      "end": 341.65,
      "text": "The assets."
    },
    {
      "start": 342.01,
      "end": 344.35,
      "text": "A-S-S-E-T-S."
    },
    {
      "start": 344.51,
      "end": 346.53,
      "text": "복수형까지 붙어 있는 표현인데."
    },
    {
      "start": 346.63,
      "end": 347.11,
      "text": "Assets."
    },
    {
      "start": 347.23,
      "end": 348.99,
      "text": "이게 자산이라는 의미죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.19,
      "end": 350.05,
      "text": "아, 이게 좋은 단어죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 350.23,
      "end": 350.93,
      "text": "Assets."
    },
    {
